Uhuru has condoled with the family, relatives and friends of Lt. Col. (Rtd) Samuel Ngure Matu following his death. He died on Sunday morning at his home in Nakuru. The 82-year-old was one of the military officers who served as the Aide De Camp (ADC) to the country’s founding President Jomo Kenyatta. In a statement on Sunday, Uhuru eulogized  Matu as a patriotic Kenyan who served the country diligently in various capacities. “We will forever cherish Lt. Col. (Rtd) Samuel Ngure Matu for his commitment to the service of our beloved country. His diligence and skills earned him a position as Chief Security Officer at Toyota Kenya Ltd after retiring from the military,” Uhuru said. Uhuru noted that Matu was a great role model and leaves behind a rich legacy that should be emulated. “We thank God for having given him to us as a gift. We appreciate his service to the community, especially the role he played in church and in the Military Officers Association,” he said. The President prayed to God to give the bereaved family strength and grace to bear the loss.